menting land use policies that encourage the dense clustering of industries. This book will be essential reading for those seeking a greater understanding of industrial growth in the province of Ontario.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aPetroleum industry and tradexGovernment policyzOntario, Southern. 0aPetroleum industry and tradezOntario, SouthernxHistory. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266313840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442663138423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442663138.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK